FBI Holds James ‘Whitey’ Bulger, Wanted for Links to 19 Murders, AP Says

-- B y   C h r i s   P e t e r s o n
-- 
2011-06-23T04:38:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-23/fbi-holds-james-whitey-bulger-wanted-for-links-to-19-murders-ap-says.html
Federal Bureau of Investigation 
agents arrested James “Whitey” Bulger, a  Boston  gang leader
wanted in connection with 19 murders, after 16 years on the run,
the  Associated Press  reported, citing Santa Monica police
spokesman Sergeant Rudy Flores.  Bulger, on the FBI’s “Ten Most Wanted” list, was captured
near  Los Angeles ; a former FBI informant, he fled Boston just
before he was to be indicted, the newswire said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Chris Peterson  at 
 cpeterson@bloomberg.net  